_:N687d6248ccbe442b86fc9658858f2ec4 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>The Rt Hon Julian Smith was Secretary of State for Northern Ireland from 24 July 2019 to 13 February 2020.</p>\n\n<p>Julian was previously Parliamentary Secretary to the Treasury (Chief Whip) from 2 November 2017 to 24 July 2019. He was Treasurer of HM Household (Deputy Chief Whip) from 13 June 2017 to 2 November 2017. He was Vice Chamberlain of HM Household (Government Whip) from 17 July 2016 to 13 June 2017.</p>\n\n<p>He was elected Conservative MP for Skipton and Ripon in 2010.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"education\">Education</h2>\n\n<p>Julian was educated at Millfield School. He read English and history at the University of Birmingham.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"politics\">Politics</h2>\n\n<p>In Parliament, Julian had a brief stint in the Scottish Affairs Committee in 2010. Julian served as an a Assistant Government Whip from May 2015 until July 2016.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"career-before-politics\">Career before politics</h2>\n\n<p>Julian was an entrepreneur before entering Parliament, setting up and leading Arq International.</p>\n" <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
